{
  "texts": [
    "The latter is important because for many purposes it is not sufficient for their to exist a capability to, for example, go to an archive to look up some information.",
    "If all members deem it too costly or not worthwhile to seek out some information, that theoretically available information is neglected and useless.",
    "The main focus of the model is whether individuals decide to invest in innovation or learning (we treat these as interchangeable) in the 'traditional' way, through a possibly cheaper AI-enabled process, or not at all.",
    "The idea is to capture, for example, the difference between someone who does extensive research in an archive rather than just relying on readily-available materials, or someone who takes the time to read a full book rather than reading a two-paragraph LLM-generated summary.",
    "Humans, unlike LLMs trained by researchers, have agency in deciding among possible inputs."
  ]
}